  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: v1.10.23\r\nprysm version: v3.1.1\r\nOS & Version: linux\r\nCommit hash : used official docker image(ethereum/client-go:v1.10.23 and gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:v3.1.1)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nthe `safe head` should only a few seconds behind the latest block.\r\nrefer here: https://blog.ethereum.org/2021/11/29/how-the-merge-impacts-app-layer\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9280285/190365576-b0ddbee9-9e64-409a-bb7b-854eeffe5c8e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9280285/190365909-132b330e-d35e-48db-8576-8f5aeea97d45.png)\r\n\r\nI don't know why the result is different with the blob, and should it means that the confirmed block number should >= 80 ?\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nJust use these below commands.\r\n```\r\neth.getBlock(\"safe\").number - eth.getBlock(\"finalized\").number\r\n\r\neth.getBlock(\"latest\").number - eth.getBlock(\"safe\").number\r\n```\r\n",
